The paper deals with generating titles for user-generated videos, which involves understanding the content of the video and summarizing it in a concise and attention-grabbing manner. This task is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), as it requires analyzing both visual and textual information. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of sentence augmentation and training methods, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the dataset used in the paper is a collection of user-generated videos, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
